{
  "texts": [
    "To predict student grades, the MsaCNN was tested on three real-world datasets from a private institute.",
    "The results of each experiment demonstrated that MsaCNN outperformed the comparison approaches on every dataset for every scenario.",
    "To continuously predict student's performance in a specific course, He et al (2020) proposed the RNN-GRU model based on student's demographics, historical data in the current course, and sequential behavior data that can fit static and sequential data.",
    "The RNN, GRU, and LSTM were utilized as they fit static and sequential data, as well as their ability to incorporate the sequential relationship of learning data.",
    "Results from experiments conducted on the Open University Learning Analytics Dataset (OULAD) revealed that the GRU outperformed the LSTM model in terms of prediction accuracy, achieving over 80% for at risk students at the end of the semester."
  ]
}